<hl>
<seg id=1> The 14 open cities along the Chinese borders have achieved great successes in economy. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, 2 February The 14 open cities along the Chinese border achieved great successes in economy in 1995. </seg>
<seg id=3> According to the statistics, these cities fulfilled the total output value of 19 billion Yuan last year that was 90% increases compared with that in 1991 before the open policy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In 1992, the State Council approved 14 cities along the Chinese border such as Heihe, Pingxiang, Hunchun, Yiling, Ruili, etc. as the open cities where 14 Economic Zones were approved to set up at the same time. </seg>
<seg id=5> Three years later, the economy of these cities grew fast and the local economic strength improved. The economy registered an average annual increase of 17% higher than that of the national average annual rate. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to the report, the construction and co-operation of the 14 cities quickened their steps. </seg>
<seg id=7> In three years, these cities invested the fixed assets of 12 billion Yuan in total. The conditions of these cities in the past such as "the buildings were not high; the roads were not smooth; the lights were not bright; the water was not clean and the traffic was not unimpeded" had changed. </seg>
<seg id=8> There were 22.6 square kilometres in the Economic Zones, and 287 joint enterprises whose foreign investment was US$890 million. </seg>
<seg id=9> In addition, there were 5100 national co-operative enterprises that had put 175 industrial projects into production. </seg>
</p>
